      • spatialFilter

        public FeatureDataStore.FeatureQueryParameters.SpatialFilter spatialFilter
        The spatial filter. Only those features whose geometry satisfies the filter will be accepted. If null no spatial filter is applied.

      • minResolution

        public double minResolution
        The minimum resolution. Only those feature sets with a maximum resolution higher than the specified value will be accepted. A value of Double.NaN indicates that there is no minimum resolution constraint.

      • maxResolution

        public double maxResolution
        The maximum resolution. Only those feature sets with a minimum resolution lower than the specified value will be accepted. A value of Double.NaN indicates that there is no maximum resolution constraint.

      • visibleOnly

        public boolean visibleOnly
        If true, only those features that are currently visible will be accepted.

      • geometryTypes

        public java.util.Collection<java.lang.Class<? extends Geometry>> geometryTypes
        The accepted geometry types. If null all geometry types will be accepted.

      • ops

        public java.util.Collection<FeatureDataStore.FeatureQueryParameters.SpatialOp> ops
        The spatial operations to be applied to the results. Operations will be performed on the returned features in iteration order.

      • order

        public java.util.Collection<FeatureDataStore.FeatureQueryParameters.Order> order
        The order to be applied to the results. Sorting will always be ascending and will take into account the ordering of the elements. If null, the order of the results is undefined.

        Note that the performance of sorting the results may depend on some sort of prior indexing being performed over the features. Sorting very large results sets when no applicable index exists may require significant time.

      • limit

        public int limit
        The limit on the number of results returned. If 0 there shall be no limit.

      • offset

        public int offset
        The offset into the result list. This argument is only applicable if limit is greater-than 0.

      • ignoredFields

        public int ignoredFields
        A bitwise-OR of the fields to be excluded; if 0, no fields are excluded (default). Fields specified as ignored may return null via their respective accessor on Feature objects returned by a cursor. Ignoring fields that are unnecessary may improve memory and CPU characteristics during query and row iteration.
